column1: # date: in the center of the calibration time window (if known)
# sensitivity: sensitivity relative to FZJ calibrator (-)
# N: neutron count rate (cph), corrected for sensor efficiency (Nr/sensitivity)
# abshum: mean absolute humidity in calibration period (g/m3)
# fp: mean correction factor for pressure in calibration period (-)
# fh: mean correction factor for humidity in calibration period (-)
# fijung: mean correction factor for temporal variability of incoming neutrons in calibration period, based on JUNG (-)
# phi: temporal correction factor from pressure, humidity, incoming (fh * fp * fijung)
# Nc: neutron count rate (cph), phi-corrected (pressure, humidity, incoming)
# biomass: above-ground dry biomass (kg/m²), treated as 0 if not available
# Nvegc: neutron count rate (cph), corrected for biomass based on Baatz et al., 2015 (cph), Nc / (1 - biomass * 0.9 / 100.)
# Nsim: "neutron intensity" as simulated by PARMA (mean over energy range 1e-6 to 1e-1 MeV)
# fi: scaling factor based on Nsim, obtained by Nsim@Marquardt/Nsim
# Nscaled: neutron count rate (cph), corrected by PARMA (Nvegc * fi, if applicable, otherwise Nc * fi)
# theta: average SWC in the sensor footprint, to be used for calibration (m³/m³)
# weq: soil water equivalent of SOM and lattice water (m³/m³)
# tocal: True if row data was used for general N0 calibration
